cs.NE, cs.AI, cs.DS, cs.GT, cs.LG

This paper is about a genetic algorithm, which is a type of optimization algorithm commonly used in machine learning and artificial intelligence. Therefore, cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also involves analyzing the time complexity of the algorithm, which could fall under cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). Additionally, the use of crossover in the algorithm could relate to cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory) and the rigorous analysis of the parameter space could relate to cs.LG (Machine Learning).
